sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as User (Browser)
    participant Caddy as Ingress (Caddy)
    participant Hub as Nudged Hub
    participant Agent as Nudged Agent
    participant Docker as Docker Daemon
    participant Container as App (e.g., Plex)

    Note over Hub, Agent: Section 3.1: Control Plane (Persistent WebSocket)
    Agent->>Hub: WS Handshake (Auth Header)
    Agent->>Hub: REGISTER { "apps": ["plex"], "ip": "100.64.0.5" }
    Hub-->>Agent: ACK

    Note over User, Container: Section 4.2: The "Hold & Wake" Flow

    User->>Caddy: HTTP GET https://plex.kn8design.com
    Caddy->>Hub: Forward Request
    
    rect rgb(255, 245, 235)
        Note over Hub: App State = STOPPED
        Hub-->>User: HTTP 200 OK (Serve Splash Screen HTML)
        Note right of User: Browser displays "Waking Up..."<br/>& connects to Hub via WS
    end

    Hub->>Agent: WS Message: WAKE { "app": "plex" }
    
    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note right of Agent: Agent Processing
        Agent->>Docker: POST /containers/plex/start
        Docker-->>Agent: 204 No Content
        
        loop Health Check (Section 2.2)
            Agent->>Container: GET http://localhost:32400
            Container-->>Agent: Connection Refused / 200 OK
        end
    end

    Agent->>Hub: WS Message: STATUS { "app": "plex", "state": "READY" }
    
    Hub->>User: WS Message: "Reload" (via Splash Screen socket)
    
    Note over User, Container: Section 3.2: Data Plane (Proxy)
    
    User->>Caddy: Browser Refreshes Page
    Caddy->>Hub: Forward Request
    Note over Hub: App State = RUNNING
    Hub->>Agent: Reverse Proxy (HTTP over VPN)
    Agent->>Container: Forward traffic to Port 32400
    Container-->>User: App Content